				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As a godlen rule you should avoid putting important information in the first 12 lines and the last 12 lines. It's also best to avoid putting some really ugly glitches there.
<br />
<br />Most emus cut 8/8 but I've heard actual TVs might cut even more, while PAL TVs will definitely cut nothing !
<br />
<br />For left/right, it's pretty much the same, you should avoid putting important information in the left/right 8 pixels or so as they might be invisible. The left/right 2 pixels will always be cut of on PAL TVs too (they aren't even rendered).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

